#Class 32. Matrices

#Matrices can only have elements of the exact same type.

#The way in which you have access to a particular number in a matrix is by putting its coordinate: A[y,x]...

#You can also access a whole row by putting the row number followed by a comma in parentheses: A[1,]...

#To have acces to a whole column, you need to put the comma after the number of the column: A[,1]...